                }
            },
            "description": "In the quest for developing efficient solar cells, we can turn to nature for inspiration: One of the protein complexes that is used in the photosynthesis cycle in plants/cyanobacteria, namely Photosystem I, is tremendously efficient in turning light into charge carriers. I worked on a microfluidics-based, fully flexible and scalable photovoltaic, using Photosystem I as an active component. The results of this project were published in ACS Applied Materials and Interfaces: ",
